-- Agile shares plunge after chairman's detention
-- By Clare Jim
-- Sun Oct 12, 2014 09:41PM EDT
-- None



HONG KONG, Oct 13 (Reuters) - Shares of Chinese developer Agile Property Holdings Ltd <3383.HK> plunged more than 20 percent on Monday after the company said its chairman had been detained.

Agile said in a statement on Friday evening chairman Chen Zhuo Lin had been required by the Kunming City prosecutor "to stay at a designated residence" since the evening of Sept 30. [ID:nL3N0S60D5]